  "body": "<!--\r\n  Note: if the issue is about documentation or the website, please file it at:\r\n  https://github.com/reactjs/reactjs.org/issues/new\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nPossibly a bug, possibly a feature.\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nCreate a reducer using `useReducer` where the action is a DOM event.\r\n\r\nAttempt to update the value by passing the updater into an event.\r\n\r\nThe event cannot be accessed, throwing an error about reusing SyntheticEvents. I assume it's the updater not running synchronously.\r\n\r\n```jsx\r\nconst valueReducer = (current, e) => e.target.value\r\n\r\nconst Example = () => {\r\n    const [value, updateValue] = useReducer(valueReducer, '')\r\n\r\n    return <>\r\n        <p>{value}</p>\r\n        <button type=\"button\" value=\"test\" onPress={updateValue}>Test</button>\r\n    </>\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nIt'd be nice if it worked\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\n\r\n16.7.0-alpha",
